      • analogAccelerometer

        public static Accelerometer analogAccelerometer(int channel,
                                                double sensitivity,
                                                double zeroValueInVolts)
        Create a new single-axis Accelerometer using the AnalogAccelerometer on the specified channel, with has the given sensitivity and zero value.
        Parameters:
        channel - the channel for the analog accelerometer
        sensitivity - the desired sensitivity in Volts per G (depends on actual hardware, such as 18mV/g or 0.018 for ADXL193)
        zeroValueInVolts - the voltage that represents no acceleration (should be determine experimentally)
        Returns:
        the accelerometer; never null

      • analogAccelerometer

        public static TwoAxisAccelerometer analogAccelerometer(int xAxisChannel,
                                                       int yAxisChannel,
                                                       double sensitivity,
                                                       double zeroValueInVolts)
        Create a new single-axis Accelerometer using two AnalogAccelerometers on the specified channels, with each have the given sensitivity and zero value.
        Parameters:
        xAxisChannel - the channel for the X-axis analog accelerometer
        yAxisChannel - the channel for the Y-axis analog accelerometer
        sensitivity - the desired sensitivity in Volts per G (depends on actual hardware, such as 18mV/g or 0.018 for ADXL193)
        zeroValueInVolts - the voltage that represents no acceleration (should be determine experimentally)
        Returns:
        the accelerometer; never null
